{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The evaluate-stage command stores grounding into a dedicated `grounding` artifact, not the `plan` artifact.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The failure boundary is artifact wiring between evaluate-stage logic and the artifact store (slot/key selection). A unit test of a pure mapper could miss real miswiring in command-to-store integration. No real OS/network/subprocess is required, and correctness does not depend on model output.","test_description":"Run evaluate-stage with an in-process artifact repository, then assert `grounding` is created/updated and `plan` is untouched by evaluate. Verify persisted keys/slots, not just returned values.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.22,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The implement-stage flow reads grounding when available and still writes its execution output to `plan`.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is cross-module orchestration (read one artifact, write another). It can be validated with deterministic fixtures and an in-process store; no real infrastructure is required. Agentic was considered, but rejected because behavior text is about routing/state handoff (“reads grounding… writes…”) rather than output quality.","test_description":"Seed `grounding` in a run-context artifact store, execute implement-stage with deterministic model/tool stubs, and assert implement consumed grounding input while writing final output only to `plan`.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Higher level rejected: no behavior text requiring model judgment quality; it specifies artifact I/O semantics." ,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.14,"Integration":0.74,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.07,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Deep-dive no longer overwrites `plan` as a redundant side effect when diagnosis already exists in issue content.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The bug is a side-effect regression at the stage-to-artifact boundary. A pure unit test may not catch accidental writes triggered by deep-dive flow wiring. No real OS/network/subprocess or real-model quality assertion is required.","test_description":"Provide issue content that already includes diagnosis, run deep-dive stage against an in-memory artifact backend, and assert no write occurs to `plan` (and no mutation timestamp/version change on `plan`).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.28,"Integration":0.63,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"Artifact lineage is preserved so implement can read the `grounding` artifact produced earlier in the same run context.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is run-context/state lineage handoff across local modules. The failure appears when producer/consumer context IDs and artifact lookup interact, which is above a single function boundary. System is not required because in-process storage/context simulation can reproduce lineage bugs; Agentic is not required because the behavior does not depend on model judgment.","test_description":"Execute evaluate (or fixture producer) to persist `grounding` under run-context A, then execute implement in the same context and assert it resolves the exact prior artifact (id/version/source lineage), failing if context/key drift occurs.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Higher levels rejected: behavior text is lineage/readability in same run context, not real infra or model-output correctness.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.18,"Integration":0.69,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.06,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"In a full multi-step agent run (`deep-dive -> write-plan/evaluate -> implement`), the final implementation plan reflects grounding produced earlier in the run.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification